## Safety Notes

- Use a current-limiting resistor with the LED.
- Do not connect motors, relays, or high-current loads directly to an Arduino output pin.
- Use a transistor or driver circuit for loads requiring more current than an Arduino GPIO pin can safely supply.
- Connect the grounds of separate power supplies when a shared control reference is required.
- Disconnect power before changing physical wiring.

